  "text": "In fact, objectives are often better expressed in real-world terms than in precise numbers. Testers often use terms like minimize, small, very large, substantially higher than, etc., to state their diagnosed objectives. These terms have a fuzzy meaning and are difficult to express precisely by numbers. Fuzzy set theory makes it possible to quantify and manipulate such human statements [CITATION_1] .",
